<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5216] groovy.sql.Sql.newInstance(Map&lt;String, Object&gt;) remove params</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5216</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;method groovy.sql.Sql.newInstance(Map&amp;lt;String, Object&amp;gt;) can be nicely used with ConfigSlurper, the problem is that it removes parameters from method call argument, so source code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def res = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ConfigSlurper().parse(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;resource/Resources.groovy&apos;&lt;/span&gt;).toURI().toURL())

files.each {
		def sql = Sql.newInstance(res.db)
		&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; something
&lt;/span&gt;		sql.close()
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;fails on second iteration due to parameters had been removed from res.db map and param &quot;url&quot; can not be found&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the solution may be changing args.remove to args.get in procedure groovy.sql.Sql.newInstance(Map&amp;lt;String, Object&amp;gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
